<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Aston Martin Valkyrie Guide</title>
  <style>
    /* General Styles */
    body {
      font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
      background: #0a0a0a; /* Dark background */
      color: #e0e0e0; /* Light text */
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 1000px;
      margin: 20px auto;
      padding: 20px;
      background: #1a1a1a; /* Slightly lighter dark background */
      box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
      border-radius: 10px;
    }

    h1, h2 {
      color: #00a859; /* Aston Martin Green */
    }

    h1 {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 3rem;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      margin-top: 30px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #00a859; /* Aston Martin Green */
      display: inline-block;
    }

    p, ul {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: #e0e0e0;
    }

    ul {
      list-style-type: none;
      padding-left: 0;
    }

    li {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      padding-left: 20px;
      position: relative;
    }

    li::before {
      content: "â€¢";
      color: #00a859; /* Aston Martin Green */
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
    }

    /* Card Styles */
    .card {
      background: #262626; /* Dark card background */
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
      padding: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
    }

    .card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-5px);
      box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
    }

    /* Images Section */
    .images {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }

    .images img {
      max-width: 60%;
      height: auto;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
      transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    }

    .images img:hover {
      transform: scale(1.05);
    }

    /* Video Section */
    .video-container {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 30px;
      padding: 20px;
      background: #262626; /* Dark background */
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    }

    .video-container iframe {
      max-width: 100%;
      height: 400px;
      border-radius: 10px;
      border: 5px solid #00a859; /* Aston Martin Green */
    }

    /* Responsive Design */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .images img {
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      .video-container iframe {
        height: 250px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: 1.8rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Aston Martin Valkyrie Guide</h1>

    <!-- Overview Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>The Aston Martin Valkyrie is a hypercar like no other. Designed in collaboration with Red Bull Advanced Technologies, the Valkyrie combines Formula 1-inspired engineering with road-legal practicality. With a naturally aspirated V12 engine and hybrid technology, the Valkyrie delivers unparalleled performance and a driving experience that pushes the boundaries of what's possible.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Key Features Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Key Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Engine:</strong> 6.5-liter naturally aspirated V12 with hybrid assistance, producing over 1,000 horsepower.</li>
        <li><strong>Top Speed:</strong> Over 250 mph (402 km/h).</li>
        <li><strong>Acceleration:</strong> 0-60 mph in just 2.5 seconds.</li>
        <li><strong>Weight:</strong> Approximately 2,270 lbs (1,030 kg) thanks to extensive use of lightweight materials.</li>
        <li><strong>Exclusivity:</strong> Limited production run of 150 units, making it one of the rarest hypercars in the world.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Performance Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Performance</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Power Output:</strong> Over 1,000 horsepower combined from the V12 engine and hybrid system.</li>
        <li><strong>Transmission:</strong> 7-speed paddle-shift gearbox.</li>
        <li><strong>Braking:</strong> Carbon-ceramic brakes for exceptional stopping power.</li>
        <li><strong>Handling:</strong> Advanced aerodynamics and active suspension for maximum grip and stability.</li>
        <li><strong>Track Capability:</strong> Designed to deliver Formula 1-level performance on the track.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Technology Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Technology</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Aerodynamics:</strong> Advanced active aerodynamics for optimal downforce and efficiency.</li>
        <li><strong>Hybrid System:</strong> Combines a V12 engine with an electric motor for instant torque and improved efficiency.</li>
        <li><strong>Lightweight Construction:</strong> Extensive use of carbon fiber, titanium, and other lightweight materials.</li>
        <li><strong>Driver-Centric Design:</strong> Formula 1-inspired cockpit with a focus on driver engagement and control.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Single Image Section -->
    <div class="images">
      <img src="https://media.astonmartin.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/95b9985ff6a55afad497115ed0e5cb54-scaled-2000x1334.jpg" alt="Aston Martin Valkyrie Image">
    </div>

    <!-- Video Section -->
    <div class="video-container">
      <h2>Learn More About the Aston Martin Valkyrie</h2>
      <iframe
        width="560"
        height="400"
        src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/a57WNM2Yhc8" <!-- Replace with a relevant Aston Martin Valkyrie video -->
        title="YouTube video player"
        frameborder="0"
        allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
        allowfullscreen
      ></iframe>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>